{"id":"428835640537739_506694259418543","type":"photo","created_time":"2013-07-16T18:12:59+0000","message":"Secretary General, Bangladesh Jamaat-e-Islami & Former Minister of Social Welfare Governments of the People\u2019s Republic of Bangladesh\r\n\r\nAli Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid has been considered as one of the key figure in the politics of Bangladesh, who played an outstanding role to form the 4 party alliances based on the spirit of Nationalism and Islamic values. 4 party alliances commenced new phase of politics, as it accommodate the majority of the population under a same platform. He is renowned for his bold steps and dynamic role in all the democratic movements of the country including the movement against the autocratic ruler Ershad and the movement for introducing non-party caretaker government system. Local media uphold a heroic image of this leader during the state of emergency in 2007, as he was the one of the visible political figure at that time to carry the regular political activities to restore the democratic political system.\r\n\r\nEducation: Born on 1st January 1948, Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid learned his primary education under the tutorship and guidance of his father, renowned scholar and religious saint of the region, Late Maulana Abdul Ali. Maulana Abdul Ali is being remembered by the people as a great saint in Faridpur. Not only that he was a struggling leader and was elected MPA (Member of Provincial Assembly) in 1965.\r\n\r\nLater, he formally admitted in Faridpur Moijuddin High School and then Faridpur Zilla School. After completion of his Secondary education he was admitted into Rajendra College and completed Higher Secondary and Secondary and graduation degree from the same institution. He obtained MA in Political Science from Chitttagong University.\r\n\r\nExtra Curricular Activities: He had been actively involved in Islamic and social works since he was a student of class eight. He was closely involved with the Islamic student movement.\r\n\r\nEarly career: Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid started his professional career as the principal of the Narayanganj Ideal School. Right now, he is discharging his duties as the chairman of the Bangladesh publications. He is also the chairman of the board of directors of oldest Bengali daily, the daily Sangram and the director of weekly Sonar Bangla. For last two years, he has been came up as the editor of another English daily named \u2018The Rising Sun\u2019.\r\n\r\nCareer in Islamic Movement: Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid joined Jamaat-e-Islami after completion of his student life. He served as Ameer of Jamaat-e-Islami Dhaka City Unit as well as a member of Central Executive Committee from 1982 to 1989. He also served as Assistant Secretary General of Jamaat-e-Islami from 1989 to 2000. On 8th December, 2000, he became the Secretary General and successfully discharging these duties till date.\r\n\r\nNational politics: He is a staunch advocate for democracy. In the past he actively participated in all political and democratic movements, mass movement of 1969 and mass movement against autocratic government in 1990 and movement for holding election under Caretaker Government from 1994 to 1996. He is still playing significant roles for strengthening the democratic process in the country.\r\n\r\nAli Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid took part in the parliament election for 3 times. He has been declared winner in the 1986 parliament election, but the then autocratic ruler finally hijacked the victory and through conducting some administrative irregularities elected his party nominee victorious in that election. Mr. Mujahid also performed duties as the district minister in charge for Madaripur district. He personally supervised various social and economical development projects in the district.\r\n\r\nHe was also involved in following national committees:\r\n\r\n    Member, National Economic Council,\r\n    Member, Executive Committee on National Economic Council,\r\n    Member, National Women Development Council,\r\n    Member, Cabinet Committee on Economic Affairs,\r\n    Member, Cabinet Committee on Public Purchase,\r\n    Member, Cabinet Committee on Women Rights,\r\n    Member, Jail Reform Committee\r\n    Member, National Purchase committee\r\n    Member, National Committee against acid and drug prevention\r\n    Member, National Committee on Micro credit\r\n    Member, National Committee on Old Age allowances\r\n    Member, National Committee on preventing Adolescence Crimes\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nHe was sworn in as a minister for Social Welfare on 10th October 2001 and successfully discharged his duties until the end of the then government\u2019s tenure.\r\n\r\nSocial Work: Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid has gained a good reputation of a selfless social worker. He contributed to the establishment and development of countless educational institutes, religions and cultural centers and Mosques across the country. In his constituency of Faridpur alone, he establishes more than 50 mosques. He played an important role in establishment of the right of the Madrasah, religious institutes\u2019, students. Because of his effort, in 2002, the then coalition government recognized Fadil (B.A) and Kamil (MA) degrees of Madrasha Education Board. He is also actively involved in numerous socio-educational and research organizations. During his tenure as a cabinet minister, the infrastructural development of the most undeveloped and neglected region Faridpur and Madaripur district was built up in the real sense of the term. Countless roads, highways, schools, colleges, Madrasahs, culverts, bridges, mosques etc. were set up, developed and repaired. He inaugurated the Haji Shariatulla bridge and a divisional social service center at Shibchar upazila of Madaripur district. Mr. Mujahid has traveled all the districts and made surprise visits in his institutions. He had curbed the rate of corruption of his ministerial officials by these tours. He also established Shishu Shodon (Orphanage) for both boys and girls in 64 districts in his tenure, which helped to bring the under-privileged and impoverished section of the society to come forth. When he started his job at social welfare ministry, it was regarded then as a low profile ministry. But ultimately, it turned into high profile one, as its budget and total allotment was rapidly increased in 5 years due to his efficiency and dynamic leadership. The ministry arranged more than 35 big programs in 5 years, in which the Prime Minister of the Government of the people\u2019s republic of Bangladesh attended and extended her hands of cooperation and guidance. Under his leadership, the first ever fair for the disabled section held in the capital in 2004. He also inaugurated a safe drinking water named \u2018Mukta\u2019 which was manufactured, commercialized by the disabled. The incomes of the water bottle item are being expended for the welfare of the disabled people as well.\r\n\r\nPublication: Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid is also a well reputed and popular author. Till now he has authored 3 valuable books which are highly praised by the readers. The books are\r\n \r\n\r\n    Ajker Musolman Islamer Dabi (Today\u2019s Muslim and the demand of Islam),\r\n    Bishshobapi Islami Andolon o Jamaat-e-Islami (Influence of Jamaat-e-Islami on world wide Islamic Movement),\r\n    Turoshko Sofor (My recent visit to Turkey)\r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\nSome of his publications have been translated into English. He also wrote many articles on Islamic teachings, socio-economic and political issues in various newspapers, journals and periodicals.\r\n\r\nMovement for Muslim Ummah: Regardless of his preoccupation he travelled about 20 countries across the world, met dignitaries and Ulama and played his part for the causes of Muslim Ummah. The countries, he visited include, among others,: Saudi Arabia, United Kingdom, France, United States, Canada, Arab Emirates, Qatar, Oman, Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Japan, Malaysia, Singapore, China, Thailand and Turkey.\r\n\r\nMarital Status: Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid married Tamanna-E-Jahan on 18th October 1973. Mrs. Tamanna-E-Jahan obtained her graduate degree from Dhaka University. At present she is the assistant Secretary of Jamaat woman wing Dhaka city unit. She is also a member of Dhaka city Jamaat Majlis-e-Shoora & also central Women Majlis-e-Shoora. Tamanna-E-Jahan is a housewife with a studious mind, who read, writes and research on various contemporary issues. Ali Ahsan Mohammad Mujahid and Mrs. Tamanna-E-Jahan are blessed with 3 sons and a daughter.","picture":"https:\/\/fbcdn-photos-b-a.akamaihd.net\/hphotos-ak-prn1\/995924_506694252751877_1485529692_s.jpg"}